I feel, that without the help of inner structure

it is ideally odd, it's so in
plus connections to 29_27 and therefore to 51_9 too
even a move to inside can be strong
who can say, why this 51 is so strong ?
yes, creates new lines, and gives life to stones, that were not active

more interesting is to find development in early stage
so, this 13th is new and may be OK?
yes YKS, it is very playable
and needs careful moves from white, but also from black
why didn't black choose this kind of 21 ?
but white has so many open lines
to play this kind of move, needs careful analysis
when you are representing your country, it is hard to evaluate should one play this kind of move here
white might win here waround 18 stone
imagine yourself to the game situation
would you try this type of 21 ?
let's put the actual outcome aside
between trying to be brave and playing safe moves without win guarantees
it is often best to be safe
21 stone is a beauty, but very risky
it may be, that white can't find correct move series
golden rule: what you can see, your opponent can see :)
what you can't see, your opponent might see :)
that's why I think Kareev though often very creative attacker,
eliminated the possibility of quick loss
and kept control, though position wasn't as strong maybe as one would hope
there is space at lower rght yet.
today's lesson is over, I apologize if it was boring time to time
